'''Thalpotentiginy''' is a [[psychology|psychological]] term applied to sexual arousal from heat or even warm weather.<ref>Evans, Rod L. ''Sex-i-con: The Ultimate X-Rated Dictionary.''  New York: Citadel, 2002. p.139</ref> It is derived from the [[Greek language|Greek]] ''thalpos'' meaning "warmth" and the [[Latin]] ''tentigo'' meaning "lust, or passion."

